"Spillman C.M., Alves O.","Dynamical seasonal prediction of summer sea surface temperatures in the Great Barrier Reef",2009,"Coral Reefs","28","1",,"197","206",,,10.1007/s00338-008-0438-8,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-59449098175&partnerID=40&md5=37f37ed298271ab9b16cc3544c2ec28f","Centre for Australian Weather and Climate Research (CAWCR), Bureau of Meteorology, 700 Collins St, Melbourne, VIC 3000, Australia","Spillman, C.M., Centre for Australian Weather and Climate Research (CAWCR), Bureau of Meteorology, 700 Collins St, Melbourne, VIC 3000, Australia; Alves, O., Centre for Australian Weather and Climate Research (CAWCR), Bureau of Meteorology, 700 Collins St, Melbourne, VIC 3000, Australia","Coral bleaching is a serious problem threatening the world coral reef systems, triggered by high sea surface temperatures (SST) which are becoming more prevalent as a result of global warming. Seasonal forecasts from coupled ocean-atmosphere models can be used to predict anomalous SST months in advance. In this study, we assess the ability of the Australian Bureau of Meteorology seasonal forecast model (POAMA) to forecast SST anomalies in the Great Barrier Reef, Australia, with particular focus on the major 1998 and 2002 bleaching events. Advance warning of potential bleaching events allows for the implementation of management strategies to minimise reef damage. This study represents the first attempt to apply a dynamical seasonal model to the problem of coral bleaching and predict SST over a reef system for up to 6 months lead-time, a potentially invaluable tool for reef managers. © 2008 Springer-Verlag.","Coral bleaching; Coupled ocean-atmosphere model; Great Barrier Reef; POAMA; Seasonal forecast; SST","atmosphere-ocean coupling; climate modeling; climate prediction; coral bleaching; damage; global warming; sea surface temperature; seasonal variation; Australasia; Australia; Coral Sea; Great Barrier Reef; Pacific Ocean; Queensland; Anthozoa",,,,,,"Alves, O., Wang, G., Zhong, A., Smith, N., Tzeitkin, F., Warren, G., Schiller, A., Meyers, G., POAMA: Bureau of Meteorology Operational Coupled Model Forecast System (2003) National Drought Forum, , Brisbane, 15/16 April; Berkelmans, R., Willis, B., Seasonal and local spatial patterns in the upper thermal limits of corals on the inshore Central Great Barrier Reef (1999) Coral Reefs, 18, pp. 219-228; Berkelmans, R., De'Ath, G., Kininmonth, S., Skirving, W., A comparison of the 1998 and 2002 coral bleaching events on the Great Barrier Reef: Spatial correlation, patterns and predictions (2004) Coral Reefs, 23, pp. 74-83; Brown, B.E., Coral bleaching: Causes and consequences (1997) Coral Reefs, 16, pp. 129-S138; Colman, R., Geographical contributions to global sensitivity in a general circulation model (2002) Glob Planet Change, 32, pp. 211-243; Colman, R.A., McAvaney, B.J., The sensitivity of the climate response of an atmospheric general circulation model to changes in convective parameterization and horizontal resolution (1995) J Geophys Res, 100, pp. 3155-3172; Done, T., Whetton, P., Jones, R., Berkelmans, R., Lough, J., Skirving, W., Wooldridge, S., (2003) Global Climate Change and Coral Bleaching on the Great Barrier Reef, p. 49. , Final Report to the State of Queensland Greenhouse Taskforce through the Department of Natural Resources and Mines; Donner, S.D., Skirving, W.J., Little, C.M., Oppenheimer, M., Hoegh-Guldberg, O., Global assessment of coral bleaching and required rates of adaptation under climate change (2005) Glob Change Biol, 11, pp. 2251-2265; Donner, S.D., Knutson, T.R., Oppenheimer, M., Model-based assessment of the role of human-induced climate change in the 2005 Caribbean coral bleaching event (2007) Proc Natl Acad Sci USA, 104, pp. 5483-5488; Fabricius, K.E., Hoegh-Guldberg, O., Johnson, J., McCook, L., Lough, J., (2007)Gleason, D.F., Wellington, G.M., Ultraviolet-radiation and coral bleaching (1993) Nature, 365, pp. 836-838; Glynn, P.W., Coral ree